pr_review_comments:
[{'comment_id': 679088019, 'comment_body': "What is a LongDomain in this context? (i.e. how long?) - I'd have assumed all our issuers should be able to sign for any domain that is within the length restrictions noted in RFCs.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 29, 12, 4, 14, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'munnerz', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 679089303, 'comment_body': "Ah, I see here that 'LongDomain' is defined as something that contains a subdomain segment that is `maxLengthOfDomainSegment` long (which I think is 63 characters) - I don't think any public ACME servers/Let's Encrypt's staging environment has a restriction on this? ðŸ¤” if it does, and the 'pebble' based ACME server does not, then Pebble needs modifying to also fail in these cases as it aims to replicate the ACME RFC as closely as possible", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 29, 12, 6, 19, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'munnerz', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 679089715, 'comment_body': 'From what I can tell, `Copy` and `List` are unused?', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 29, 12, 6, 59, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'munnerz', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 679091340, 'comment_body': 'Ah, I see `Copy` is used in some of your new code below - my bad!', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 29, 12, 9, 29, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'munnerz', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 679134936, 'comment_body': "The issue is with Let's Encrypt specifically rather than the ACME protocol. There's a discussion here: https://github.com/certbot/certbot/issues/1915

Let's encrypt copies one of the names from the subject alternative name (which supports arbitrary length domains) to the Common Name field (which is useless in modern TLS). Unfortunately, this field has a maximum length of 64 `char`s (C definition, so bytes).

This isn't a problem with cert-manager as we don't set the subject CN at all", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2021, 7, 29, 13, 9, 34, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'jakexks', 'type': 'User'}]
